.TH "hpt3x3_init_one" 9 "hpt3x3_init_one" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
hpt3x3_init_one \- Initialise an HPT343/363
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" hpt3x3_init_one
.BI "(struct pci_dev *pdev "  ","
.BI "const struct pci_device_id *id "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pdev" 12
PCI device
.IP "id" 12
Entry in match table

Perform basic initialisation. We set the device up so we access all
ports via BAR4. This is necessary to work around errata.
